      "question": "A tower stands vertically on the ground. From a point on the ground, which is $15$ m away from the foot of the tower, the angle of elevation of the top of the tower is found to be $60^\\circ$. The height of the tower is:",
      "answer": "(C)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Let the height of the tower be $h$.",
          "In the right triangle, $\\tan(60^\\circ) = \\frac{\\text{height}}{\\text{base}}$.",
          "Substitute the values: $\\sqrt{3} = \\frac{h}{15}$.",
          "Solve for $h$."
        ],
        "derivation": "\\tan(60^\\circ) = \\frac{h}{15} \\implies \\sqrt{3} = \\frac{h}{15} \\implies h = 15\\sqrt{3} \\text{ m}"
      },
      "topic": "Some Applications of Trigonometry",
