      "question": "A kite is flying at a height of $60$ m above the ground. The string attached to the kite is temporarily tied to a point on the ground. The inclination of the string with the ground is $30^\\circ$. The length of the string is:",
      "answer": "(D)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Let $L$ be the length of the string.",
          "In the right triangle, $\\sin(30^\\circ) = \\frac{\\text{height}}{\\text{hypotenuse}}$.",
          "Substitute the values: $\\frac{1}{2} = \\frac{60}{L}$.",
          "Solve for $L$."
        ],
        "derivation": "\\sin(30^\\circ) = \\frac{60}{L} \\implies \\frac{1}{2} = \\frac{60}{L} \\implies L = 120 \\text{ m}"
      },
