      "question": "The angle of elevation of the top of a pole from a point on the ground $20$ m away from the foot of the pole is $45^\\circ$. The height of the pole is:",
      "answer": "(B)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Let $h$ be the height of the pole.",
          "Use the relation $\\tan(45^\\circ) = \\frac{h}{20}$.",
          "Since $\\tan(45^\\circ) = 1$, we have $1 = \\frac{h}{20}$."
        ],
        "derivation": "\\tan(45^\\circ) = \\frac{h}{20} \\implies 1 = \\frac{h}{20} \\implies h = 20 \\text{ m}"
