    {
      "question": "If the length of the shadow of a tower is $\\sqrt{3}$ times the height of the tower, then the angle of elevation of the sun is:",
      "answer": "(A)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Let the height of the tower be $h$. Then the shadow length is $h\\sqrt{3}$.",
          "Let $\\theta$ be the angle of elevation.",
          "Use $\\tan(\\theta) = \\frac{h}{h\\sqrt{3}}$.",
          "Simplify to find $\\theta$."
        ],
        "derivation": "\\tan(\\theta) = \\frac{h}{h\\sqrt{3}} = \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}} \\implies \\theta = 30^\\circ"
      },
