      "question": "An observer $1.5$ m tall is $28.5$ m away from a chimney. The angle of elevation of the top of the chimney from her eyes is $45^\\circ$. The height of the chimney is:",
      "answer": "(C)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Height of observer = $1.5$ m. Distance = $28.5$ m.",
          "Height of chimney above observer's eye level = $28.5 \\times \\tan(45^\\circ) = 28.5$ m.",
          "Total height = $28.5 + 1.5$."
        ],
        "derivation": "H = 28.5 + 1.5 = 30 \\text{ m}"
